description.plain: Emerging artist and internet sensation DripReport has ignited a grassroots global phenomenon with his viral hit single “Skechers”. Inspired by the love of his South Asian roots, along with popular internet culture, DripReport is carving out a new lane within music and social media. Building a cult following by creating remixes of popular American hit records, DripReport accumulated hundreds of millions of views across his YouTube and social platforms. He then released his first single “Skechers” in January, a song that is now trending worldwide. “My goal is to combine my cultures into something that people around the world can relate to,” says DripReport. “I want to help globalize our culture in a way that’s easily consumed around the world. It’s about bringing people together and making them feel happy when listening to my music.” With organic, fan-driven support for “Skechers,” DripReport is doing just that.

songs.title: Skechers

description.plain:
“Skechers” is a song about a man who fell in love at first sight. He cannot remember much about her besides the fact that she wore Light-up Skechers, which are a type of sneaker. He talks about how he’s rich and he’ll buy her things in exchange for nudes.
This song became very popular due to many people using the song on the popular video making app known as TikTok.

songs.title: Skechers (Remix)

description.plain:
Drip enlists Tyga on the remix of his January 2020 track “Skechers,” which is a song about a man who fell in love at first sight.

The track was first previewed on Tyga’s TikTok account on May 2, 2020.  The track was officially announced on May 14, 2020, with its artwork, a day before its release.

songs.full_title: XXXTENTACION - Moonlight (Indian Version Cover) by DripReport
songs.title: XXXTENTACION - Moonlight (Indian Version Cover)

description.plain:
“Moonlight (Indian Version Cover)” is a cover of XXXTENTACION’s March 2018 song, “Moonlight.”

DripReport’s Indian version cover of the song benefited from the posthumous popularity of the original song over the internet, which, as a result,  became one of his most popular covers ever. The original video lasted under a minute, therefore the YouTube channel Goated Beats made a longer version of the song, extending it to about two minutes.
